    "title": "Capability ceiling sweep @ 32768 tokens (rebuilt from io_corpus)",
    "text": "Capability measured at a NON-BINDING 32768-token ceiling, 2 samples/cell, temperature 0. A cell is PASS only if every sample passed and none truncated; disagreement is UNSTABLE, never a majority-vote pass. `truncations > 0` OR `errors > 0` for a model means that model has holes in its measurement and NO capability verdict is licensed for it.\n\nREBUILT FROM io_corpus: the sweep process was killed during its (low-value) budget-walk phase before it emitted a note, and its conditions block would have omitted timeout_s anyway. Every capability call is in the corpus keyed by ticket_id=eval:<query>; this note is reconstructed from those 128 records and verified with the SAME EvalQuery.verify() the sweep used.\n\nHEADLINE: deepseek-r1:14b (a $0 local model) clears the whole b5_frontier band and fails b4-boxes. deepseek-r1:32b fails b5-frobenius (also at 4096 and 8192, clean stop). The 32b's capability set is NOT a superset of the 14b's, so the >= ladder that difficulty_meets asserts is unsound. deepseek-v3.1:671b-cloud has NO verdict on b5-frobenius: it HUNG, twice.",
